The paper discusses a method for visualizing and understanding the behavior of learned agents in deep reinforcement learning, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), game theory (cs.GT), and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper specifically focuses on generating more focused saliency maps to explain agent behavior, which involves analyzing and interpreting the features of the input state that are most relevant for the agent in taking an action. This is a common problem in machine learning and AI research, and the paper's approach could be relevant to a wide range of applications in these fields.
